
# 📄 HTML & CSS Documentation – Tourism Website

This document explains all the **HTML elements** and **CSS properties** used in the Tourism Website project.

---

## 🏗️ HTML Elements Used

### 1. Structural Elements

* `<!DOCTYPE html>` → Defines HTML5 document type.
* `<html>` → Root element of the page.
* `<head>` → Holds metadata, stylesheets, and scripts.
* `<body>` → Contains all visible webpage content.
* `<div>` → Used extensively as **containers** for grouping and styling content.

### 2. Head & Linking

* `<link>` → Imports external CSS (Bootstrap & custom stylesheet).
* `<script>` → Loads JavaScript files (Bootstrap JS, jQuery, custom scripts).
* `<title>` → (Optional) Sets the title of the web page.

### 3. Text Content

* `<h1>` → Main headings (e.g., "Tourism", "Favourite Places", "Detailed View").
* `<p>` → Paragraph text (descriptions of tourist places).

### 4. Interactive Elements

* `<button>` → Used for navigation (Get Started, Back buttons, etc.).
* `onclick` attribute → Calls JavaScript functions to switch sections (`display('sectionid')`).

### 5. Images

* `<img>` → Displays place images and carousel slides with `src`, `alt`, and `class` attributes.

### 6. Bootstrap Components

* `<div class="carousel ...">` → Bootstrap **carousel (slideshow)** component.
* `<ol>` & `<li>` → Indicators for carousel navigation.
* `<a>` → Carousel navigation controls (Next, Previous).
* `<span>` → Icons for carousel controls.

---

## 🎨 CSS Properties Used

### 1. Background Styling

* `background-image` → Adds background images (`ocean.jpg`, `towerbg.png`, `seabg.png`).
* `background-size: cover;` → Ensures the image covers the entire container.
* `background-color` → Sets background color (used for cards and buttons).

### 2. Box Model

* `min-height`, `height`, `width` → Controls element dimensions.
* `margin` → Creates space around elements.
* `padding` → Creates space inside elements.
* `border-radius` → Rounds the corners of cards and buttons.
* `border-width` → Removes or customizes borders (used on buttons).

### 3. Typography

* `font-family: "Roboto";` → Sets the text font.
* `font-size` → Defines text size (50px for headings, 18px for details, etc.).
* `font-weight` → Makes text bold (e.g., headings).
* `color` → Sets text color (white/black).
* `text-align` → Aligns text (`center`, `start`, `justify`).

### 4. Flexbox (Bootstrap + Custom)

* `display: flex;` (`d-flex`) → Enables flexible box layout.
* `flex-direction: column` / `row` → Defines arrangement direction.
* `justify-content: end` → Aligns items horizontally or vertically.

### 5. Image Styling

* `height`, `width` → Adjust image dimensions.
* `padding` → Adds spacing inside image containers.

### 6. Button Styling

* `color` → Sets text color on buttons (white).
* `background-color: #25b1cc;` → Custom button background (blue).
* `width`, `height` → Defines button size.
* `border-radius: 20px;` → Rounded button edges.
* `font-size: medium;` → Adjusts button text size.

---
